OL,6,FWinchester Crown Court heard how
OL,7,FOliver entered the address holding a
OL,8,Fhammer before searching the house for
OL,9,Fhis former business partner, with whom
OL,10,Fhe had become involved in a civil
OL,11,Fdispute which resulted in Oliver being
OL,12,Fordered to pay a significant amount of
OL,13,Fmoney.
OL,15,FThe men grappled with each other
OL,16,Fbefore Oliver punched the victim in
OL,17,Fthe neck and body whilst wearing a
OL,18,Fmeat claw.
